summary: This is an email from an unspecified sender to a recipient at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS), transmitting revised versions (v6 and v7) of a government document, likely a Motion In Limine (MIL), with the note that paralegals cannot assist with cite-checking.
keyFacts: An email was sent on October 18, 2021, regarding revised government motions in limine (MILs).
The communication was directed to the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York (USANYS).
Attached documents included a clean version and a redlined comparison of government MIL versions 6 and 7.
The email notes that paralegals are unable to assist with cite-checking the documents.
